metadata.name: dg5721() #97
metadata.description:
A tiny neural network with 5721 neurons, that tries to imitate human handwriting by generating new hallucinated digits in real-time.

It can generate these digits at any resolution and will invent its own ways to fill the gaps.

- Press <SPACE> or click to toggle the infinite latent space exploration.
- Press <S> to save the current frame as PNG at the current screen resolution x2.

It can be installed to work offline (Install button in the URL bar in Chrome or "Add to Home screen" on iOS)

As of 2021, this artwork requires a fast computer or mobile phone.

metadata.name: Window gratings #18
metadata.description:
Window gratings were once a ubiquitous sight in Taiwan. Starting around the 1950s, homeowners began installing stylized metal barriers in front of their windows to keep out thieves.

The artwork focused on window gratings and add some fantastic colors & materials.
Wait for seconds and you'll see time flies.

100,000 possible buildings & floors combinations  
20 different color palette + 20 monotone (20%)
9 unique Window grating styles
6 door styles
4 roof and 4 fence styles
3 room styles

[keyboard] Press 's' to save PNG in original size

metadata.name: Tree Rings #162
metadata.description:
Experimenting with organic movement. Each ring is meant to show the differing growth patterns the tree may have from year to year and what sort of nutrients it's received.

Each Tree Ring has 1 - 9 rings, with 200 - 1000 radians, each ring and background selected from a library of 64 colors.

metadata.name: ALL SEEING #65
metadata.description:
ALL SEEING explores the distribution of human eye colors by mapping color probabilities to each mint. Every artwork is different. Eye positioning, color, stroke and density is determined by a random seed hash. Color probability is loosely based on distribution across the human population, but weighted slightly to allow more color drops. For a lucky few, eyes become multicolored. If the hash gives it's blessing, there's a STAR MAN waiting in that rarest ~1% of mints that features a red background and a near fully-dialated pupil.

--- Features ---
Random eye color distributions of brown ~51% ,blue ~20%, hazel ~10%, amber ~5%, gray ~5%, green ~5%, heterochromia ~3%, and STAR MAN ~1%
Color density
White density
